{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.11",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 11 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:1",
      "text": "The wisdom of the lowly will lift up his head, and make him sit in the midst of great men.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:2",
      "text": "Don’t commend a man for his good looks. Don’t abhor a man for his outward appearance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:3",
      "text": "The bee is little among flying creatures, but what it produces is the best of confections.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:4",
      "text": "Don’t boast about the clothes you wear, and don’t exalt yourself in the day of honor; for the Lord’s works are wonderful, and his works are hidden among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:5",
      "text": "Many kings have sat down upon the ground, but one who was never thought of has worn a crown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:6",
      "text": "Many mighty men have been greatly disgraced. Men of renown have been delivered into other men’s hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:7",
      "text": "Don’t blame before you investigate. Understand first, and then rebuke.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:8",
      "text": "Don’t answer before you have heard. Don’t interrupt while someone else is speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:9",
      "text": "Don’t argue about a matter that doesn’t concern you. Don’t sit with sinners when they judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:10",
      "text": "My son, don’t be busy about many matters; for if you meddle much, you will not be unpunished. If you pursue, you will not overtake, and you will not escape by fleeing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:11",
      "text": "There is one who toils, labors, and hurries, and is even more behind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:12",
      "text": "There is one who is sluggish, and needs help, lacking in strength, and who abounds in poverty, but the Lord’s eyes looked upon him for good, and he raised him up from his low condition,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:13",
      "text": "and lifted up his head so that many marveled at him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:14",
      "text": "Good things and bad, life and death, poverty and riches, are from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:17",
      "text": "The Lord’s gift remains with the godly. His good pleasure will prosper forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:18",
      "text": "One grows rich by his diligence and self-denial, and this is the portion of his reward:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:19",
      "text": "when he says, “I have found rest, and now I will eat of my goods!” he doesn’t know how much time will pass until he leaves them to others and dies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:20",
      "text": "Be steadfast in your covenant and be doing it, and grow old in your work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:21",
      "text": "Don’t marvel at the works of a sinner, but trust the Lord and stay in your labor; for it is an easy thing in the sight of the Lord to swiftly and suddenly make a poor man rich.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:22",
      "text": "The Lord’s blessing is in the reward of the godly. He makes his blessing flourish in an hour that comes swiftly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:23",
      "text": "Don’t say, “What use is there of me? What further good things can be mine?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:24",
      "text": "Don’t say, “I have enough. What harm could happen to me now?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:25",
      "text": "In the day of good things, bad things are forgotten. In the day of bad things, a man will not remember things that are good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:26",
      "text": "For it is an easy thing in the sight of the Lord to reward a man in the day of death according to his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:27",
      "text": "The affliction of an hour causes delights to be forgotten. In the end, a man’s deeds are revealed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:28",
      "text": "Call no man happy before his death. A man will be known in his children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:29",
      "text": "Don’t bring every man into your house, for many are the tricks of a deceitful man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:30",
      "text": "Like a decoy partridge in a cage, so is the heart of a proud man. Like a spy, he looks for your weakness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:31",
      "text": "For he lies in wait to turn things that are good into evil, and assigns blame in things that are praiseworthy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:32",
      "text": "From a spark of fire, a heap of many coals is kindled, and a sinful man lies in wait to shed blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:33",
      "text": "Take heed of an evil-doer, for he plans wicked things, lest perhaps he ruin your reputation forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.11.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 11:34",
      "text": "Receive a stranger into your house, and he will distract you with arguments and estrange you from your own family.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
